  "body": "**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nIn v1.3.8 of the Helm chart, an expression which checks `.Values.agent.mountSecurityMode` in `templates/clusterrole.yaml` is changed. When `.Values.agent` is defined, it no longer checks if `.Values.agent.mountSecurityMode` is also defined before comparing it to `\"Any\"`. This causes a `error calling ne: invalid type for comparison` error when Helm tries to parse the chart, because nil cannot be compared to a string this way.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nWhen `.Values.agent` is there, but `.Values.agent.mountSecurityMode` is not, we expect it to default to an empty string as well, so it can be compared to `\"Any\"`.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\nSupply a `.Values.agent` value, but not `.Values.agent.mountSecurityMode` (for example by only defining `.Values.agent.nodeSelector`, which is how I encountered the problem).\r\n",
